00:40:35,371 --> 00:40:38,250
because unlike you, I never
abandon my weak students

525
00:40:38,731 --> 00:40:39,686
Bye, sir

526
00:40:41,692 --> 00:40:42,726
Quiet;

527
00:40:45,172 --> 00:40:46,240
Quiet, I said

528
00:40:49,572 --> 00:40:52,802
I regret to inform you
that your son...

529
00:40:52,931 --> 00:40:54,001
Farhan...
Raju...

530
00:40:54,251 --> 00:40:55,286
has fallen into bad company

531
00:40:55,612 --> 00:40:58,648
Without urgent corrective steps,
his future will be ruined

532
00:40:59,692 --> 00:41:02,842
Virus 's letters dropped on
our homes like atom bombs

533
00:41:03,132 --> 00:41:05,487
Hiroshima and Nagasaki
plunged into gloom

534
00:41:05,572 --> 00:41:08,530
Our parents invited us -
for a dressing down

535
00:41:09,532 --> 00:41:11,601
Come in

536
00:41:14,052 --> 00:41:14,961
See that?

537
00:41:16,291 --> 00:41:18,760
We could afford
just one air-conditioner

538
00:41:20,452 --> 00:41:23,967
We put it in Farhan's room,
so he could study in comfort

539
00:41:25,371 --> 00:41:29,159
I didn't buy a car.
I manage with a scooter

540
00:41:30,012 --> 00:41:31,809
We put all our money
into Farhan's education

541
00:41:33,251 --> 00:41:37,210
We sacrificed our comforts
for Farhan's future. U nderstand?

542
00:41:45,492 --> 00:41:46,811
You took these pictures, Farhan?

543
00:41:48,652 --> 00:41:50,563
He had that useless
obsession for a while

544
00:41:51,492 --> 00:41:53,083
Went around taking
pictures of animals

545
00:41:53,172 --> 00:41:55,844
Wanted to be a
wildlife photographer

546
00:41:57,012 --> 00:41:59,320
Son, what was your
score that year?

547
00:42:00,251 --> 00:42:01,400
91%

548
00:42:01,731 --> 00:42:06,202
Hear that? Straight drop
from 94% to 91%

549
00:42:09,211 --> 00:42:10,610
You find it funny?

550
00:42:11,251 --> 00:42:15,164
No sir, sorry. I'm just
amazed at the photos

551
00:42:15,331 --> 00:42:17,846
Why make him an engineer...
Why not a wildlife photographer?

552
00:42:18,012 --> 00:42:19,126
Enough;

553
00:42:20,331 --> 00:42:25,405
I humbly request you -
Don't ruin my son's future

554
00:42:26,851 --> 00:42:29,126
Food's on the table, boys. C'mon

555
00:42:33,851 --> 00:42:36,047
If you ever visit again,
do eat with us

556
00:42:38,851 --> 00:42:40,251
Dad denied us a meal...

557
00:42:40,811 --> 00:42:42,403
So, to fill our bellies with food...

558
00:42:42,771 --> 00:42:45,922
and ears with more reprimands,
we reached Raju's house

559
00:42:47,811 --> 00:42:51,724
Raju's house was straight
out of a 50's black and white film

560
00:42:52,452 --> 00:42:53,407
A small, dingy room...

561
00:42:53,572 --> 00:42:55,005
a paralyzed father...

562
00:42:55,771 --> 00:42:56,920
a coughing mother...

563
00:42:57,291 --> 00:42:58,724
and an unwed sister

564
00:42:59,811 --> 00:43:01,130
A sofa sprouting springs...

565
00:43:01,572 --> 00:43:03,766
a 24 hour water supply -
from the leaking roof

566
00:43:04,411 --> 00:43:07,882
Mother was a retired school
teacher and a tireless complainer

567
00:43:08,532 --> 00:43:10,601
Father was once a postmaster

568
00:43:11,092 --> 00:43:13,400
Paralysis shut down
his body partly...

569
00:43:13,851 --> 00:43:16,161
his salary completely.
And the sister...

570
00:43:16,331 --> 00:43:19,802
Kammo's turned 28.
They demand a car in dowry

571
00:43:20,411 --> 00:43:22,925
If you don't study and earn,
how will she marry?

572
00:43:23,411 --> 00:43:24,288
Some okra?

573
00:43:25,251 --> 00:43:28,960
Okra is now 12 /- per kilo,
cauliflower is 10/-

574
00:43:29,291 --> 00:43:30,644
It's daylight robbery;

575
00:43:31,012 --> 00:43:34,846
What will we eat if we get
warnings from your college?

576
00:43:35,092 --> 00:43:35,967
Mom!

577
00:43:37,492 --> 00:43:38,402
Cottage cheese?

578
00:43:38,851 --> 00:43:42,242
Cottage cheese should be sold
at the jewelers, in velvet pouches

579
00:43:42,532 --> 00:43:44,250
Cottage cheese?
- No, no, it's ok

580
00:43:44,891 --> 00:43:46,371
Mom, please

581
00:43:47,211 --> 00:43:48,929
Alright, I'll shut up

582
00:43:50,532 --> 00:43:54,844
Earn for the family,
slave like a maid

583
00:43:55,052 --> 00:43:57,246
and then take the vow of silence

584
00:43:58,172 --> 00:44:02,528
If not with my son, with whom
do I share my woes: his friends?

585
00:44:06,291 --> 00:44:07,327
Hey Raju

586
00:44:10,731 --> 00:44:11,721
We were in a huge dilemma

587
00:44:12,331 --> 00:44:15,324
Do we comfort our friend
or console his mom?

588
00:44:16,492 --> 00:44:19,324
Screw it, we thought, let's
focus on the cottage cheese

589
00:44:30,771 --> 00:44:33,490
Even his eczema cream
costs 55 /- now

590
00:44:38,052 --> 00:44:39,326
Another roti?

591
00:44:39,652 --> 00:44:42,485
No, thank you. We're through

592
00:44:49,972 --> 00:44:52,440
Okra for 12 /-
- Cauliflower for 10 /-

593
00:44:55,371 --> 00:44:57,123
At least you were offered a meal

594
00:44:57,931 --> 00:45:00,684
Unlike your sadistic dad...
'Hitler' Qureshi;

595
00:45:00,811 --> 00:45:03,405
And your mom is Mother Teresa...
Feeding us 'eczema roti'!

596
00:45:03,652 --> 00:45:07,088
Don't poke fun at my mom;
- Enough, you guys

597
00:45:07,371 --> 00:45:08,724
I'm famished. Let's eat out

598
00:45:08,851 --> 00:45:11,126
It's month end. Who'll pay?
His Mother Teresa?

599
00:45:12,132 --> 00:45:16,523
To eat out, you don't need money.
Just a uniform. Look...

600
00:45:19,211 --> 00:45:20,804
C'mon
- Come

601
00:45:22,331 --> 00:45:24,481
Good evening,
good evening

602
00:45:24,572 --> 00:45:25,402
Oh, U ncle

603
00:45:30,492 --> 00:45:33,608
Three large vodkas.
- Half soda, half water

604
00:45:33,811 --> 00:45:35,005
If we're caught, we're dead

605
00:45:35,172 --> 00:45:37,606
What's for starters?
- Get double portions

606
00:45:37,692 --> 00:45:40,603
Leave this here and start
some peppy music

607
00:45:41,331 --> 00:45:42,923
Pia, what the hell!

608
00:45:43,291 --> 00:45:45,885
Why're you wearing
this ancient piece of junk?

609
00:45:47,052 --> 00:45:50,487
What'll people say: My fiancee...

610
00:45:50,891 --> 00:45:53,360
a doctor in the making,
wearing a cheap, 200 /- watch;

611
00:45:54,251 --> 00:45:55,684
Please take it off. Thank you

612
00:45:56,211 --> 00:45:57,201
Hi handsome

613
00:45:57,331 --> 00:46:00,050
Hey Aunty.
You're looking good

614
00:46:00,132 --> 00:46:02,599
Don't miss my set, darling
- Rubies?

615
00:46:02,771 --> 00:46:05,286
From Mandalay
- Mandalay... Wow;

616
00:46:05,371 --> 00:46:07,965
Hey, let's go meet David
- Of course

617
00:46:11,012 --> 00:46:12,047
Excuse me

618
00:46:14,132 --> 00:46:15,246
Yes?

619
00:46:15,532 --> 00:46:16,567
Flowers

620
00:46:18,012 --> 00:46:21,083
May I take the glass?
- Why?

621
00:46:21,371 --> 00:46:23,567
So you don't break it on my head

622
00:46:24,331 --> 00:46:25,525
Why would I do that?

623
00:46:25,931 --> 00:46:27,967
For the free advice I'll now impart

624
00:46:29,092 --> 00:46:29,922
What?

625
00:46:30,251 --> 00:46:31,764
Don't marry that ass

626
00:46:32,811 --> 00:46:33,688
Excuse me?

627
00:46:33,891 --> 00:46:35,530
He's not a human,
he's a price tag

628
00:46:35,931 --> 00:46:38,809
He'll turn your life into a
nightmare of brands and prices

629
00:46:39,411 --> 00:46:41,880
He'll ruin your life.
Your future will be finished

630
00:46:42,172 --> 00:46:43,001
Want a demonstration?

631
00:46:45,092 --> 00:46:46,650
Shall I find out
the price of his shoes?

632
00:46:48,132 --> 00:46:49,963
I won't ask.
He'll announce it himself

633
00:47:01,532 --> 00:47:07,242
What the hell...
Mint sauce on my $300 shoes!

634
00:47:07,371 --> 00:47:10,443
Run for your life;
It's free advice. Take it or leave it

635
00:47:10,972 --> 00:47:13,565
Genuine Italian leather -
hand-stitched;

636
00:47:17,972 --> 00:47:20,565
Dad, are they your guests?

637
00:47:23,771 --> 00:47:26,922
My students.
What're they doing here?

638
00:47:30,731 --> 00:47:31,880
Hold on, Dad

639
00:47:33,371 --> 00:47:35,521
These beans smell great

640
00:47:35,652 --> 00:47:37,882
No room for roti
- Just pile it on

641
00:47:39,771 --> 00:47:41,090
Hi
- Hey

642
00:47:42,572 --> 00:47:45,449
That was an eye-opener.
Thank you so much

643
00:47:46,891 --> 00:47:49,086
It was my moral responsibility

644
00:47:49,851 --> 00:47:51,204
Can I ask you for little more help?

645
00:47:52,251 --> 00:47:54,766
Dad won't let me break off
this engagement

646
00:47:55,692 --> 00:47:59,525
You explain so well.
Can you give him a demo too?

647
00:47:59,811 --> 00:48:02,326
Certainly.
Raju, the mint sauce

648
00:48:02,851 --> 00:48:04,251
You're really sweet

649
00:48:05,411 --> 00:48:08,369
Where is your daddy?
- Right behind you

650
00:48:12,811 --> 00:48:15,041
Aal izz well

651
00:48:15,811 --> 00:48:20,760
Run for your life;
It's free advice. Take it or leave it

652
00:48:21,052 --> 00:48:22,530
What're you doing here?

653
00:48:23,132 --> 00:48:26,123
We'll hand these gifts
to the couple

654
00:48:27,132 --> 00:48:29,327
I'll do that for you.
It's my sister's wedding

655
00:48:29,731 --> 00:48:30,847
Sister?

656
00:48:33,572 --> 00:48:35,880
Sir, what's the sum total
of your daughters?

657
00:48:37,411 --> 00:48:38,242
Empty. No gift cheques

658
00:48:38,572 --> 00:48:40,563
Forgot the cheques, Raju
...Farhan?

659
00:48:40,652 --> 00:48:44,644
We didn't invite you,
you must be from the groom's side

660
00:48:45,132 --> 00:48:48,920
No sir, we're here as the
emissaries of science

661
00:48:49,052 --> 00:48:51,168
How? Can you explain?

662
00:48:51,411 --> 00:48:54,927
Dad, he explains superbly.
I'm sure he'll give us a demo

663
00:48:55,211 --> 00:48:56,121
Won't you?

664
00:48:56,931 --> 00:49:00,367
Well, Delhi has plenty of
power cuts that...

665
00:49:00,612 --> 00:49:02,842
disrupt wedding celebrations

666
00:49:03,172 --> 00:49:05,208
So I thought of making
an inverter that...

667
00:49:05,331 --> 00:49:07,641
draws power from guests' cars

668
00:49:07,851 --> 00:49:09,170
I see

669
00:49:09,371 --> 00:49:10,804
Wow

670
00:49:11,172 --> 00:49:12,525
So where's the inverter?

671
00:49:13,291 --> 00:49:14,849
Sir, the design is ready

672
00:49:17,811 --> 00:49:19,039
Where's the design, Farhan?

673
00:49:19,452 --> 00:49:22,364
I gave you the design
- I gave it to Raju

674
00:49:22,771 --> 00:49:23,681
Raju, design?

675
00:49:26,652 --> 00:49:30,246
Never mind the design.
I'll make the inverter and show you

676
00:49:30,572 --> 00:49:34,086
You can only invent stories,
not an inverter

677
00:49:34,371 --> 00:49:37,329
I'll make one, I promise

678
00:49:37,652 --> 00:49:41,007
And I'll name it after you.
After all, it was invented...

679
00:49:41,411 --> 00:49:44,768
at your daughter's wedding.
So it'll be an honor...

680
00:49:44,891 --> 00:49:50,682
Farhan, Raju. I'll see you
in my office tomorrow

681
00:49:56,331 --> 00:49:59,688
Sir, what was the cost per plate?
We'll reimburse you

682
00:50:00,012 --> 00:50:01,603
...in installments

683
00:50:03,972 --> 00:50:07,088
We'll never crash a wedding again
- Not even my own

684
00:50:07,211 --> 00:50:09,362
In fact, I won't even marry.
Nor will he

685
00:50:10,012 --> 00:50:11,967
Uh... right. No marriage

686
00:50:13,411 --> 00:50:15,686
Your parents shouldn't have
married either

687
00:50:17,291 --> 00:50:19,726
The world would have
to feed two less idiots

688
00:50:22,132 --> 00:50:23,121
Sit!

689
00:50:33,692 --> 00:50:34,681
Pay attention

690
00:50:45,172 --> 00:50:49,927
This is Ranchhoddas's father's
monthly income

691
00:50:51,211 --> 00:50:57,286
Couple of zeroes less,
and it's still a sizeable income

692
00:50:59,731 --> 00:51:05,806
But erase another zero,
and I would worry a little

693
00:51:07,012 --> 00:51:10,242
Isn't that your father's income,
Farhan?

694
00:51:11,092 --> 00:51:12,730
Yes, sir

695
00:51:14,052 --> 00:51:16,007
Now take away another zero...

696
00:51:18,931 --> 00:51:22,561
and that's your family income,
Raju Rastogi

697
00:51:23,692 --> 00:51:25,010
Big reason to worry

698
00:51:29,532 --> 00:51:36,403
Take my advice and shift into
Chatur Ramalingam's room

699
00:51:36,811 --> 00:51:40,885
Exams are here. Stay with
Rancho and you're sure to fail

700
00:52:01,931 --> 00:52:04,240
Want a shave?
- No, sir

701
00:52:04,411 --> 00:52:05,242
Then get lost!

702
00:52:16,052 --> 00:52:21,409
Raju, don't worry. This is Virus's
move to split us. Divide and rule

703
00:52:21,532 --> 00:52:22,567
I have to worry

704
00:52:22,972 --> 00:52:26,327
He grades us, and I need
good grades for a good job

705
00:52:27,211 --> 00:52:30,123
Unlike you, I don't have a
rich dad I can live off

706
00:52:30,251 --> 00:52:32,048
Shut up, Raju

707
00:52:32,291 --> 00:52:34,851
Must we follow all his hogwash?
'Aal izz well'

708
00:52:35,211 --> 00:52:36,610
I won't be his flunky... like you

709
00:52:37,532 --> 00:52:39,726
You're crossing the line
- No, I'm drawing one

710
00:52:40,211 --> 00:52:41,849
I have a family to support

711
00:52:43,972 --> 00:52:46,121
Dad's medicines
swallow up mom's pension

712
00:52:48,012 --> 00:52:52,210
My sis can't marry because
they want a car in dowry

713
00:52:55,012 --> 00:52:59,085
Mom hasn't bought a
single saree in five years

714
00:53:01,811 --> 00:53:04,884
Now don't get your mom's
wardrobe into the debate

715
00:53:05,972 --> 00:53:07,882
By the way, how many sarees
per annum is reasonable?

716
00:53:08,931 --> 00:53:10,126
Hey... no wisecracks about mom

717
00:53:10,851 --> 00:53:14,925
We'll study with all our heart,
but not just for grades

718
00:53:15,572 --> 00:53:19,724
To quote a Wise One: Study
to be accomplished, not affluent

719
00:53:20,452 --> 00:53:25,764
Follow excellence. And success
will chase you, pants down;

720
00:53:26,931 --> 00:53:29,445
Which Wise One says this?
His Holiness Guru Ranchhoddas?

721
00:53:31,411 --> 00:53:32,367
Go rot in the bogs;

722
00:53:33,931 --> 00:53:36,809
Raju, don't stress. We'll top
our class. Nothing is impossible

723
00:53:37,092 --> 00:53:38,206
Oh yeah?

724
00:53:41,731 --> 00:53:43,768
Shove this back into the tube

725
00:53:46,692 --> 00:53:48,250
Raju got onto another train

726
00:53:48,771 --> 00:53:53,721
His travails with Chatur began.
Yes, I mean travails, not travels

727
00:53:57,972 --> 00:53:59,802
Chatur was called 'Silencer'

728
00:54:00,132 --> 00:54:03,681
To sharpen his memory,
he popped pills from a local quack

729
00:54:04,092 --> 00:54:05,969
And then let off silent...
but lethal farts

730
00:54:08,572 --> 00:54:11,643
I didn't do it... Raju?

731
00:54:11,811 --> 00:54:14,371
He always blamed others
for the output

732
00:54:15,092 --> 00:54:17,844
Silencer crammed 18 hours a day

733
00:54:18,092 --> 00:54:21,083
On exam eve,
he would distract others

734
00:54:24,891 --> 00:54:27,849
His belief: There are only
two ways of topping

735
00:54:28,172 --> 00:54:31,322
Elevate your own grades or
shrink your opponents' grades

736
00:54:35,452 --> 00:54:39,161
Rancho decided to subdue
Silencer and rescue Raju...

737
00:54:39,612 --> 00:54:40,840
with one master plan

738
00:54:42,811 --> 00:54:50,492
Our Director has unceasingly
served... 'Served' means...

739
00:54:50,572 --> 00:54:54,451
Damn the meaning,
I'll memorize it

740
00:54:55,811 --> 00:54:59,282
Chatur was the introductory speaker
at the Teachers' Day function

741
00:54:59,612 --> 00:55:03,365
To impress Virus, he got his
speech written by the librarian...

742
00:55:03,572 --> 00:55:04,846
in highbrow Hindi

743
00:55:06,331 --> 00:55:11,485
Hello. Hold on.
Chatur, call for you

744
00:55:11,851 --> 00:55:14,161
Please collect the printout.
I'll be right back

745
00:55:15,492 --> 00:55:18,643
Oh... the things I have to do...

746
00:55:22,092 --> 00:55:25,128
Mr. Dubey, the Director was
remembering you

747
00:55:25,251 --> 00:55:26,764
Really?
- Yes. Just now

748
00:55:27,132 --> 00:55:30,362
I'll see him right away.
Give this to Chatur

749
00:55:35,331 --> 00:55:38,244
Hello. Hello
- Hello, Mr. Ramalingam?

750
00:55:38,371 --> 00:55:39,248
Yes?

751
00:55:39,811 --> 00:55:42,086
I'm calling from the police station

752
00:55:42,452 --> 00:55:45,170
Are you from Uganda?
- Yes sir

753
00:55:46,652 --> 00:55:49,563
Your life is in danger
- What? ... How?

754
00:55:50,652 --> 00:55:52,369
Listen carefully, or else...

755
00:55:52,972 --> 00:55:57,123
you'll get killed as you step out
of the college gate

756
00:55:57,851 --> 00:55:59,045
Why? What happened?

757
00:55:59,172 --> 00:56:00,684
While Chatur was kept engaged

758
00:56:01,092 --> 00:56:04,925
Rancho altered a few words
in his speech, for eg...

759
00:56:05,132 --> 00:56:07,407
'served' became 'screwed'

760
00:56:08,211 --> 00:56:09,440
Yes sir?

761
00:56:09,972 --> 00:56:12,405
Who are you?
- Dubey. Librarian

762
00:56:14,891 --> 00:56:16,007
I'm permanent staff, sir

763
00:56:16,612 --> 00:56:17,965
Congratulations

764
00:56:18,371 --> 00:56:21,603
Hold on a moment.
The chief is on the other line

765
00:56:21,972 --> 00:56:22,882
Excuse me, sir

766
00:56:32,172 --> 00:56:34,322
Yes... so where was I?

767
00:56:34,572 --> 00:56:36,880
You said I may die...
outside the gate

768
00:56:37,012 --> 00:56:43,166
Right. As you get out of the gate,
you'll see a traffic signal

769
00:56:43,371 --> 00:56:45,327
Traffic signal. Ok

770
00:56:45,532 --> 00:56:50,844
When it turns red,
all the cars will halt

771
00:56:51,331 --> 00:56:52,606
Ok. Then?

772
00:56:52,731 --> 00:56:54,643
Then cross the road
with great caution

773
00:56:55,371 --> 00:57:00,400
Because son, in rush hour
