But we can't leave him alone

1019
01:15:36,492 --> 01:15:39,164
I'm here.
It's a matter of three hours

1020
01:15:39,252 --> 01:15:41,811
Take my scooter.
It's getting late

1021
01:15:42,252 --> 01:15:43,240
Hey...

1022
01:15:47,488 --> 01:15:48,806
Gosh, what an ancient watch

1023
01:15:55,087 --> 01:15:55,997
Go

1024
01:16:13,368 --> 01:16:15,676
Sorry, we're late
- It was an emergency

1025
01:16:21,328 --> 01:16:22,396
Settle down there

1026
01:16:26,768 --> 01:16:27,962
Sir, they're still writing

1027
01:16:29,328 --> 01:16:30,886
Hello. Time up

1028
01:16:31,688 --> 01:16:34,202
Please, five minutes.
We started half an hour late

1029
01:16:34,368 --> 01:16:35,516
It was an emergency

1030
01:16:35,608 --> 01:16:39,725
He glared at us like we 'd
asked for both his kidneys

1031
01:16:40,887 --> 01:16:42,002
But we continued writing

1032
01:16:42,927 --> 01:16:45,840
He continued arranging
the answer sheets

1033
01:16:54,007 --> 01:16:54,884
Done, sir

1034
01:16:55,847 --> 01:16:58,362
You're late.
I can't accept these

1035
01:16:58,568 --> 01:16:59,398
Sir, please, sir

1036
01:17:03,768 --> 01:17:05,042
Sir, do you know who we are?

1037
01:17:06,448 --> 01:17:08,199
Prime Ministers son?
Even then...

1038
01:17:08,488 --> 01:17:10,479
I will not accept your paper

1039
01:17:11,927 --> 01:17:13,838
Do you know
our names and roll numbers?

1040
01:17:15,087 --> 01:17:16,157
No...

1041
01:17:17,927 --> 01:17:18,917
Who are you?

1042
01:17:19,007 --> 01:17:20,918
He doesn't know: Run!

1043
01:17:22,528 --> 01:17:24,722
Hey, what's your roll number?

1044
01:17:25,488 --> 01:17:29,605
Where the hell are their papers?

1045
01:17:33,927 --> 01:17:35,680
O Lord, have mercy

1046
01:17:35,768 --> 01:17:41,319
Today was Results day.
Time to make a deal with God

1047
01:17:41,448 --> 01:17:43,837
Just save my Electronics.
I'll offer a coconut

1048
01:17:44,287 --> 01:17:48,997
Sir Snake, bless my Physics.
I promise a pint of milk per day

1049
01:17:49,207 --> 01:17:52,484
O Mother Cow,
help me pass... have this grass

1050
01:17:52,728 --> 01:17:55,925
I vow: No X-rated thoughts
of girls in my class...

1051
01:17:56,207 --> 01:17:57,606
Watch over my results

1052
01:17:57,807 --> 01:18:01,516
God of Wealth, I'll offer 100 /-
every month

1053
01:18:01,728 --> 01:18:04,242
100 /- won't bribe even a traffic cop

1054
01:18:04,927 --> 01:18:06,680
let alone the Almighty

1055
01:18:07,847 --> 01:18:09,838
Check from the bottom

1056
01:18:10,807 --> 01:18:12,844
You are... last

1057
01:18:14,488 --> 01:18:15,363
And you?

1058
01:18:17,328 --> 01:18:18,726
Second last

1059
01:18:20,247 --> 01:18:21,283
Rancho?

1060
01:18:25,528 --> 01:18:26,563
Not there

1061
01:18:27,887 --> 01:18:28,877
My heart sank

1062
01:18:29,448 --> 01:18:33,680
Not 'cause our ranks tanked,
but 'cause our friend flunked

1063
01:18:36,047 --> 01:18:39,596
There's a mistake.
It's not possible. It's injustice

1064
01:18:43,568 --> 01:18:46,365
What's Silencer howling about?

1065
01:18:46,967 --> 01:18:47,877
He got the second rank

1066
01:18:49,728 --> 01:18:51,127
Who's first?

1067
01:18:52,287 --> 01:18:53,356
Rancho

1068
01:18:55,768 --> 01:18:56,962
Rancho?

1069
01:18:59,328 --> 01:19:00,123
Move aside

1070
01:19:04,728 --> 01:19:06,922
We learned a lesson
in Human Behavior:

1071
01:19:07,688 --> 01:19:12,841
Your friend fails, you feel bad.
Your friend tops, you feel worse

1072
01:19:13,528 --> 01:19:17,760
We were sad.
Two others were sadder

1073
01:19:18,967 --> 01:19:22,676
Ranchhoddas Chanchad.
Front row. Right of the Director

1074
01:19:23,287 --> 01:19:25,483
Uday Sinha. Second row. Third seat

1075
01:19:26,368 --> 01:19:29,484
Alok Mittal. Second row. Fifth seat

1076
01:19:31,207 --> 01:19:33,768
Sahili Rao. Third row...

1077
01:19:33,927 --> 01:19:36,283
Sir, why this seating
according to rank?

1078
01:19:37,408 --> 01:19:38,601
Any problem with that?

1079
01:19:38,728 --> 01:19:42,686
Yes, this grading system is
like a caste system

1080
01:19:43,127 --> 01:19:46,164
A-graders: Masters
C-graders: Slaves

1081
01:19:46,448 --> 01:19:49,599
It's not nice, sir
- You have a better idea?

1082
01:19:50,167 --> 01:19:54,161
Yes. Results should not be
displayed at all

1083
01:19:54,608 --> 01:19:58,520
Why publicise someone's flaws?

1084
01:19:58,807 --> 01:20:03,643
If your iron count is low,
will the doctor prescribe tonic...

1085
01:20:03,768 --> 01:20:05,167
or air your report on TV

1086
01:20:05,967 --> 01:20:07,002
You see, sir?

1087
01:20:07,568 --> 01:20:09,286
So basically,
what you are saying is

1088
01:20:09,768 --> 01:20:11,485
I should personally go to
each student's room

1089
01:20:12,488 --> 01:20:13,523
and whisper in his ears...

1090
01:20:14,528 --> 01:20:16,837
'You have come first';
'You're second';

1091
01:20:16,927 --> 01:20:18,440
'Oh, I'm so sorry,
you have failed'

1092
01:20:21,328 --> 01:20:25,525
No sir, I mean
grades create a divide

1093
01:20:27,768 --> 01:20:29,645
I've topped, so I'm next to you

1094
01:20:29,887 --> 01:20:32,197
My pals came last,
they're in the back corner

1095
01:20:32,368 --> 01:20:33,846
At least they're in the corner

1096
01:20:33,967 --> 01:20:36,277
More time with you, and
they'll be out of the photo

1097
01:20:37,368 --> 01:20:39,279
They will neither pass,
nor get a job

1098
01:20:40,047 --> 01:20:43,756
They'll get jobs, sir.
There must be some firm that...

1099
01:20:44,207 --> 01:20:45,960
prefers humans to machines

1100
01:20:47,768 --> 01:20:49,520
They'll get jobs. I guarantee

1101
01:20:51,448 --> 01:20:53,677
You guarantee it;

1102
01:20:53,887 --> 01:20:55,367
Bet, sir?

1103
01:20:58,608 --> 01:20:59,881
Govind
- Yes, sir?

1104
01:21:03,887 --> 01:21:07,038
Even if one of them gets
a job in campus interviews...

1105
01:21:08,207 --> 01:21:09,356
shave off my moustache

1106
01:21:12,007 --> 01:21:12,837
Sir!

1107
01:21:13,127 --> 01:21:16,039
Happy?
- Smile, please

1108
01:21:17,287 --> 01:21:18,198
Happy, sir

1109
01:21:22,967 --> 01:21:25,845
Jackass;
Honking to hide your tooting

1110
01:21:26,368 --> 01:21:28,962
Septic tank; Popping pills again?

1111
01:21:29,207 --> 01:21:31,768
I didn't do it... Raju?

1112
01:21:31,967 --> 01:21:33,525
This is a familiar stink

1113
01:21:33,608 --> 01:21:36,520
He's the sole cause for
global warming

1114
01:22:00,768 --> 01:22:03,282
Toss me your wallet: I'll buy pants

1115
01:22:03,847 --> 01:22:07,841
Take Chatur's suit instead
- Don't touch my suit

1116
01:22:08,967 --> 01:22:10,685
Rancho'll recognize you
even in underwear

1117
01:22:10,847 --> 01:22:14,681
Where's this?
- If I could read, would I sell peanuts?

1118
01:22:14,887 --> 01:22:17,355
He can't read
- But he can speak

1119
01:22:17,568 --> 01:22:21,402
Wait. Do you know a
Ranchhoddas Chanchad?

1120
01:22:21,608 --> 01:22:23,279
Yes, he lives there

1121
01:22:23,927 --> 01:22:29,047
Free as the wind was he

1122
01:22:30,967 --> 01:22:36,167
Like a soaring kite was he

1123
01:22:37,768 --> 01:22:39,962
Where did he go...

1124
01:22:40,167 --> 01:22:42,318
let's find him

1125
01:22:42,448 --> 01:22:45,007
Chatur, your pills
- Thanks. Where were they?

1126
01:22:45,047 --> 01:22:47,481
In the pocket
- Hey, my pants!

1127
01:22:47,608 --> 01:22:49,519
Karl Marx says to
share all resources

1128
01:22:51,047 --> 01:22:52,925
Hey, you'll give people ideas

1129
01:22:54,408 --> 01:22:55,396
I want it now

1130
01:23:10,047 --> 01:23:11,117
What happened?

1131
01:23:13,167 --> 01:23:14,317
Rancho's father

1132
01:23:17,688 --> 01:23:20,327
Excuse me,
where is Ranchhoddas?

1133
01:23:21,127 --> 01:23:23,436
There he is
- Thank you

1134
01:23:45,688 --> 01:23:48,725
Rancho...
- Yes?

1135
01:23:49,287 --> 01:23:52,837
Sorry. We're looking for Ranchhoddas

1136
01:23:53,807 --> 01:23:55,082
I am Ranchhoddas

1137
01:23:55,648 --> 01:23:59,402
No, I mean... 'Ranchhoddas
Shamaldas Chanchad'

1138
01:24:00,768 --> 01:24:03,235
Ranchhoddas Shamaldas
Chanchad. That's me

1139
01:24:08,488 --> 01:24:10,682
Ranchhoddas, take care, son

1140
01:24:29,207 --> 01:24:31,243
'Ranchhoddas Chanchad'

1141
01:24:38,127 --> 01:24:39,117
Raju

1142
01:25:03,368 --> 01:25:06,837
I'll be in the Guinness Book for
driving Delhi-Shimla in underwear

1143
01:25:06,967 --> 01:25:08,037
That too, for the wrong guy;

1144
01:25:08,528 --> 01:25:12,315
Same name, same degree,
same photo, but a different guy

1145
01:25:12,847 --> 01:25:14,280
What's going on?

1146
01:25:14,967 --> 01:25:17,528
How did Silencer get
Rancho's address?

1147
01:25:18,648 --> 01:25:19,478
Good point!

1148
01:25:20,847 --> 01:25:22,201
Hey Chatur, come here

1149
01:25:28,247 --> 01:25:31,604
How dare you open this?
I got this from San Francisco

1150
01:25:31,648 --> 01:25:33,127
Handmade biscuits

1151
01:25:34,847 --> 01:25:37,042
Specially for Mr. Phunsukh Wangdu

1152
01:25:37,287 --> 01:25:39,358
Phunsukh Bangdu?
Who's that?

1153
01:25:39,448 --> 01:25:43,838
Not Bangdu. Wangdu. 'W'.
Phunsukh Wangdu

1154
01:25:43,967 --> 01:25:46,686
Do you know who that is?
He's a great scientist

1155
01:25:46,768 --> 01:25:49,362
400 patents.
The world wants him

1156
01:25:50,368 --> 01:25:53,677
Took me a year
to get an appointment

1157
01:25:54,408 --> 01:25:59,640
Once he signs the deal with
my company, I'll be huge!

1158
01:25:59,728 --> 01:26:03,720
Forget Wangdu.
How'd you get Rancho's address?

1159
01:26:03,847 --> 01:26:05,725
You should be thanking
Phunsukh Wangdu

1160
01:26:06,087 --> 01:26:09,524
He led me to Rancho, See this

1161
01:26:11,608 --> 01:26:15,840
My secretary was here to fix
an appointment with Wangdu

1162
01:26:15,967 --> 01:26:20,119
She didn't get the appointment.
But I found Rancho

1163
01:26:20,247 --> 01:26:25,640
I checked the Shimla directory
and found Rancho's name

1164
01:26:25,688 --> 01:26:27,279
What happened to his face?

1165
01:26:27,648 --> 01:26:29,842
Plastic surgery
in honor of your visit?

1166
01:26:34,087 --> 01:26:35,840
Only one man has the answer

1167
01:26:36,408 --> 01:26:40,845
Sorry Papa,
I couldn't fulfill your last wish

1168
01:26:42,287 --> 01:26:45,917
You kept asking me
to take you on pilgrimage

1169
01:26:46,807 --> 01:26:49,197
But I waited
for the highway tender

1170
01:26:50,648 --> 01:26:54,926
There the tender opened,
here you closed your eyes

1171
01:26:58,847 --> 01:27:03,159
I am so sorry, Papa.
I could not be a good son...

1172
01:27:03,328 --> 01:27:04,601
Wrong

1173
01:27:05,047 --> 01:27:07,766
You're an engineer.
Your degree's on the wall!

1174
01:27:08,047 --> 01:27:09,275
You were a very good son

1175
01:27:11,807 --> 01:27:16,359
How dare you barge in?
I'll have you arrested

1176
01:27:16,528 --> 01:27:19,600
No, you'll be arrested.
We've made enquiries

1177
01:27:19,847 --> 01:27:22,840
You use the degree
to clinch contracts

1178
01:27:23,287 --> 01:27:26,404
It's our friend's degree.
How did you get it?

1179
01:27:41,368 --> 01:27:42,720
This is a 150 acre estate

1180
01:27:43,127 --> 01:27:46,199
If I shoot and bury you,
no one would even notice

1181
01:27:46,528 --> 01:27:47,404
Get the point?

1182
01:27:48,688 --> 01:27:49,518
Now get lost

1183
01:27:54,847 --> 01:27:59,000
I'm taking Papa's ashes to the
sacred river. Can take yours too

1184
01:28:06,167 --> 01:28:07,680
Grab Papa!

1185
01:28:10,488 --> 01:28:11,556
Here, here

1186
01:28:15,528 --> 01:28:16,516
Let go of Papa;

1187
01:28:19,328 --> 01:28:22,046
Tell the truth or
Papa is flushed;

1188
01:28:22,167 --> 01:28:24,966
Hand over Papa
- Papa goes to the sacred sewer

1189
01:28:25,648 --> 01:28:28,845
Get Papa out of the potty
- You pull trigger, I pull flush.

1190
01:28:28,967 --> 01:28:30,242
I'll count to three

1191
01:28:30,287 --> 01:28:33,837
Wanna shoot us?
Raju, scatter the ashes

1192
01:28:36,448 --> 01:28:37,403
One

1193
01:28:37,568 --> 01:28:42,118
Take us down,
and Papa's down the drain

1194
01:28:43,328 --> 01:28:44,203
Two

1195
01:28:44,287 --> 01:28:46,643
Then grope for him in the gutter

1196
01:28:46,768 --> 01:28:47,597
What is it, Raju?

1197
01:28:48,967 --> 01:28:51,356
We've got the wrong urn.
It's empty;

1198
01:28:52,207 --> 01:28:53,083
Empty?

1199
01:28:54,408 --> 01:28:57,717
Empty: we'll empty it out;

1200
01:28:57,847 --> 01:28:58,677
No, no;

1201
01:28:58,768 --> 01:29:01,520
We'll empty it out

1202
01:29:01,608 --> 01:29:03,962
No... hands up!

1203
01:29:06,167 --> 01:29:09,079
Who are you?

1204
01:29:09,247 --> 01:29:10,317
I am Rancho

1205
01:29:11,568 --> 01:29:13,922
I swear on Papa, it's true

1206
01:29:14,127 --> 01:29:15,845
I am Rancho;
That was Chhote.

1207
01:29:16,927 --> 01:29:17,724
Chhote?

1208
01:29:19,047 --> 01:29:23,837
He was our gardener's son, Chhote

1209
01:29:25,728 --> 01:29:28,447
He stayed on with us
after he was orphaned

1210
01:29:30,568 --> 01:29:38,077
Did odd jobs around the house,
ran errands

1211
01:29:39,448 --> 01:29:40,676
He had a passion for learning

1212
01:29:43,807 --> 01:29:46,368
He'd wear my old uniform
and slip into school

1213
01:29:48,287 --> 01:29:51,121
And attend any class he liked.
It suited me

1214
01:29:52,047 --> 01:29:57,838
I made him do my homework,
take my exams

1215
01:29:58,368 --> 01:30:01,279
It was going well, till
one day...

1216
01:30:01,688 --> 01:30:06,078
Our teacher saw a sixth grader
doing tenth grade math

1217
01:30:06,127 --> 01:30:07,606
Which grade are you in, son?

1218
01:30:08,768 --> 01:30:09,917
What's your name?

1219
01:30:10,847 --> 01:30:11,757
We got caught

1220
01:30:12,847 --> 01:30:14,201
Papa was a powerful man, so...

1221
01:30:14,328 --> 01:30:17,684
our teacher alerted him
before going to the Principal

1222
01:30:18,167 --> 01:30:21,956
You started it, you will finish it

1223
01:30:24,568 --> 01:30:27,240
People pretend to show me respect

1224
01:30:27,927 --> 01:30:30,043
But behind my back...

1225
01:30:30,967 --> 01:30:32,525
mock me as an illiterate

1226
01:30:33,488 --> 01:30:35,444
I won't let that happen to my son

1227
01:30:36,488 --> 01:30:40,640
This boy wants to study.
I want just a degree

1228
01:30:41,167 --> 01:30:43,045
Let the game go on

1229
01:30:44,007 --> 01:30:45,565
Make this kid an engineer

1230
01:30:46,768 --> 01:30:51,921
and I'll have a degree
in my son's name on that wall

1231
01:30:52,247 --> 01:30:56,082
I went to London for four years,
he went to college as me

1232
01:30:57,688 --> 01:31:03,604
He'd promised to cut contact with all
after getting the degree

1233
01:31:05,568 --> 01:31:13,805
But he always said,
'Two idiots will come looking for me'

1234
01:31:18,328 --> 01:31:19,920
He really misses you both

1235
01:31:22,247 --> 01:31:26,036
I'll give you his address,
go to him

1236
01:31:29,247 --> 01:31:32,604
But please keep my secret

1237
01:31:34,408 --> 01:31:35,523
What secret?

1238
01:31:48,328 --> 01:31:51,684
You got the wrong urn, sir.
Papa is in here

1239
01:31:53,807 --> 01:31:56,275
What the hell's going on?
Who was that gun guy?

1240
01:31:56,328 --> 01:31:59,717
Complicated story.
Without subtitles. Not for you

1241
01:31:59,768 --> 01:32:01,962
Ignore it
- Where're we going?

1242
01:32:03,247 --> 01:32:04,123
Ladakh

1243
01:32:04,167 --> 01:32:05,487
Ladakh! Why?

1244
01:32:06,167 --> 01:32:07,078
To meet Rancho

1245
01:32:07,247 --> 01:32:10,126
What's he doing in Ladakh?

1246
01:32:10,167 --> 01:32:13,604
No clue. We have
the address of a school

1247
01:32:13,847 --> 01:32:16,805
School teacher!

1248
01:32:17,648 --> 01:32:20,923
I'm Vice President of
Rockledge Corporation, and he...

1249
01:32:21,328 --> 01:32:23,523
A for Apple, B for Ball...

1250
01:32:23,688 --> 01:32:24,837
D for Donkey

1251
01:32:25,528 --> 01:32:30,283
Next week I sign a huge deal
with Phunsukh Wangdu

1252
01:32:30,448 --> 01:32:33,359
And he... A for Apple, B for Ball...

1253
01:32:36,927 --> 01:32:39,237
Today my respect
for that idiot shot up

1254
01:32:40,127 --> 01:32:42,358
Most of us went to college
just for a degree

1255
01:32:42,927 --> 01:32:46,966
No degree meant
no plum job, no pretty wife...

1256
01:32:47,247 --> 01:32:49,716
no credit card, no social status

1257
01:32:50,368 --> 01:32:52,119
None of this mattered to him

1258
01:32:52,247 --> 01:32:54,000
He was in college
for the joy of learning

1259
01:32:54,488 --> 01:32:57,639
He never cared
if he was first or last

1260
01:32:58,207 --> 01:33:00,438
Who was the first man
on the Moon?

1261
01:33:00,688 --> 01:33:01,837
Neil Armstrong, sir

1262
01:33:01,927 --> 01:33:03,997
Obviously, it is Neil Armstrong.
We all know it

1263
01:33:04,167 --> 01:33:05,362
Who was the second?

1264
01:33:05,847 --> 01:33:07,405
Don't waste your time.
It's not important

1265
01:33:07,847 --> 01:33:10,237
Nobody remembers the man
who ever came second

1266
01:33:11,328 --> 01:33:16,560
Soon, 26 companies
will be here with job offers

1267
01:33:17,007 --> 01:33:22,445
You'll have a job
even before your final exam

1268
01:33:23,167 --> 01:33:24,965
This is your last lap, my friends

1269
01:33:25,287 --> 01:33:27,404
Put the pedal to the metal.
Step on the gas

1270
01:33:27,488 --> 01:33:29,399
