01:52:45,688 --> 01:52:51,842
We're not done yet... no way

1530
01:52:52,047 --> 01:52:58,157
We won't let go of you

1531
01:52:58,328 --> 01:53:04,085
We're not done yet... no way

1532
01:53:04,127 --> 01:53:10,363
We won 't let go of you

1533
01:53:10,688 --> 01:53:12,359
'Okra Rs.12 / kilo'

1534
01:53:21,287 --> 01:53:22,801
You called for a taxi?

1535
01:53:22,847 --> 01:53:24,565
I did
- It's waiting

1536
01:53:24,688 --> 01:53:26,121
Thank you. Why?

1537
01:53:26,528 --> 01:53:27,801
I'm going to the job interview

1538
01:53:28,047 --> 01:53:29,242
You coming with me?

1539
01:53:29,608 --> 01:53:34,045
No. I'm going for the interview.
You're going home

1540
01:53:34,167 --> 01:53:35,487
Why would I go home?

1541
01:53:36,927 --> 01:53:40,238
Remember, we promised
this rascal

1542
01:53:43,448 --> 01:53:45,439
Give me your tie

1543
01:53:46,927 --> 01:53:47,757
Why?

1544
01:53:47,967 --> 01:53:51,721
I doubt you'll go for the
interview after reading this

1545
01:53:52,608 --> 01:53:53,484
What's that?

1546
01:53:53,648 --> 01:53:56,400
A letter
- For you, from Hungary

1547
01:53:56,728 --> 01:53:59,242
Some photographer
called Andre Istvan

1548
01:54:06,847 --> 01:54:08,565
You posted my letter!

1549
01:54:08,728 --> 01:54:10,365
He loved your pictures

1550
01:54:10,807 --> 01:54:13,368
The guy wants you to assist him...

1551
01:54:14,127 --> 01:54:17,518
in the Brazilian rain forest,
for a year

1552
01:54:17,847 --> 01:54:19,405
Will pay you, too

1553
01:54:34,688 --> 01:54:35,916
Dad will never agree

1554
01:54:38,408 --> 01:54:40,967
Go speak to him...
from your heart

1555
01:54:42,568 --> 01:54:43,682
For once, dump your fears...

1556
01:54:44,328 --> 01:54:50,118
or someday, on your deathbed,
you'll regret it

1557
01:54:50,608 --> 01:54:53,076
You'll remember that the letter was
in your hand, taxi at the gate...

1558
01:54:53,207 --> 01:54:56,837
With just a little courage, you
could've turned your life around

1559
01:55:03,127 --> 01:55:05,005
Do you think he'll like it?

1560
01:55:05,608 --> 01:55:07,837
Why such an expensive gift?

1561
01:55:08,927 --> 01:55:11,283
Our son's getting
his first job today

1562
01:55:12,528 --> 01:55:16,282
Don't be stingy at
such a proud moment

1563
01:55:18,127 --> 01:55:19,082
Farhan?

1564
01:55:23,967 --> 01:55:26,162
Don't you have
the job interview today?

1565
01:55:27,847 --> 01:55:28,724
I didn't go

1566
01:55:31,368 --> 01:55:33,039
I don't want to be
an engineer, Dad

1567
01:55:37,087 --> 01:55:38,965
What happened?
You had an accident?

1568
01:55:42,448 --> 01:55:47,475
See that building?
I jumped from its third floor

1569
01:55:50,167 --> 01:55:51,043
Why?

1570
01:55:51,368 --> 01:55:53,597
Because I was rusticated
from college

1571
01:55:56,408 --> 01:55:57,203
Why?

1572
01:55:57,688 --> 01:56:02,318
Drunk, I urinated
on the Director's door

1573
01:56:04,528 --> 01:56:08,042
That scoundrel Rancho
is messing with your mind!

1574
01:56:08,167 --> 01:56:11,762
I don't enjoy Engineering.
I'd make a terrible engineer

1575
01:56:13,807 --> 01:56:18,244
Rancho has a simple belief -
Make your passion your profession

1576
01:56:18,568 --> 01:56:20,081
Then work will become play

1577
01:56:20,207 --> 01:56:22,038
What'll you earn in that jungle?

1578
01:56:22,648 --> 01:56:26,162
A small stipend, but I'll learn a lot

1579
01:56:26,207 --> 01:56:27,356
Five years from now...

1580
01:56:28,047 --> 01:56:32,599
when you see your friends buying
cars and homes, you'll curse yourself

1581
01:56:32,688 --> 01:56:36,521
Life as an engineer will bring
only frustration. Then I'll curse you

1582
01:56:38,488 --> 01:56:40,206
I'd rather curse myself, Dad

1583
01:56:40,328 --> 01:56:41,476
The world will laugh!

1584
01:56:42,688 --> 01:56:44,599
Label you a loser,
for quitting in the final year

1585
01:56:45,448 --> 01:56:50,920
Mr. Kapoor feels you're fortunate
to be at ICE. What'll he think?

1586
01:56:51,167 --> 01:56:53,238
Mr. Kapoor didn't provide me
with an air-conditioner

1587
01:56:55,927 --> 01:56:58,122
It wasn't Mr. Kapoor who slept
in discomfort while I slept well

1588
01:57:00,368 --> 01:57:03,246
He didn't take me around the zoo
on his shoulders

1589
01:57:05,967 --> 01:57:07,162
You did all that, Dad

1590
01:57:09,528 --> 01:57:14,761
How you feel, matters to me.
Mr. Kapoor makes no difference

1591
01:57:15,847 --> 01:57:17,679
I don't even know his first name

1592
01:57:17,807 --> 01:57:20,605
You think you're the hero
of a melodrama?

1593
01:57:20,768 --> 01:57:23,407
Enough, please... he's upset

1594
01:57:24,608 --> 01:57:26,962
God forbid, if he did
something crazy like Raju...

1595
01:57:27,167 --> 01:57:28,680
Then the discussion is over

1596
01:57:28,967 --> 01:57:32,596
Don't say a word or
His Lordship will jump off the roof

1597
01:57:35,927 --> 01:57:40,717
No, Dad. I'll never attempt suicide.
I promise

1598
01:57:43,127 --> 01:57:49,840
The Rancho you detest
put this picture in my wallet

1599
01:57:51,368 --> 01:57:55,042
Told me to see it if a suicidal thought
crossed my mind

1600
01:57:55,167 --> 01:57:58,319
and imagine what'd happen
to your smiles

1601
01:57:58,368 --> 01:58:00,086
when you see my dead body

1602
01:58:05,408 --> 01:58:09,037
I want to convince you, Dad

1603
01:58:10,448 --> 01:58:12,802
but not with a suicide threat

1604
01:58:16,408 --> 01:58:20,082
Dad, what'll happen
if I become a photographer?

1605
01:58:20,368 --> 01:58:21,561
I'll earn less

1606
01:58:22,448 --> 01:58:24,086
I'll have a smaller house,
a smaller car

1607
01:58:26,047 --> 01:58:27,527
But I'll be happy

1608
01:58:29,127 --> 01:58:30,355
I will be really happy

1609
01:58:31,608 --> 01:58:33,199
Whatever I do for you
will be out of genuine love

1610
01:58:35,047 --> 01:58:36,720
I've always listened to you

1611
01:58:37,087 --> 01:58:40,079
For once,
let me listen to my heart

1612
01:58:42,087 --> 01:58:42,963
Please... Dad

1613
01:58:49,127 --> 01:58:50,037
Dad...

1614
01:58:51,207 --> 01:58:52,402
Please don't go away...

1615
01:58:58,368 --> 01:58:59,516
Return this

1616
01:59:02,847 --> 01:59:05,237
Son, what's the cost
of a professional camera?

1617
01:59:06,448 --> 01:59:08,166
Can the laptop be exchanged for it?

1618
01:59:09,568 --> 01:59:11,364
If you need more money, just ask

1619
01:59:19,807 --> 01:59:21,685
Go live your life, my son

1620
01:59:24,488 --> 01:59:28,605
Your grades are consistently poor.
Reason?

1621
01:59:29,247 --> 01:59:30,078
Fear

1622
01:59:31,127 --> 01:59:32,480
I was a good student
since childhood

1623
01:59:33,207 --> 01:59:35,278
Parents hoped
I'd end their poverty

1624
01:59:37,127 --> 01:59:38,082
That scared me

1625
01:59:39,528 --> 01:59:42,837
Here I saw the mad race.
You don't count if you're not first

1626
01:59:44,528 --> 01:59:45,516
My fear grew

1627
01:59:47,127 --> 01:59:48,527
Fear is not good for grades, sir

1628
01:59:49,127 --> 01:59:51,436
I slipped on more
charms and rings

1629
01:59:52,408 --> 01:59:56,685
Prayed to God for favors.
No... begged for favors

1630
01:59:59,648 --> 02:00:02,640
16 broken bones gave me
two months to think and reflect

1631
02:00:03,167 --> 02:00:04,362
Finally, sense dawned

1632
02:00:05,807 --> 02:00:10,756
Today I didn't beg God for this job,
just thanked him for this life

1633
02:00:13,127 --> 02:00:16,962
If you reject me, no regrets

1634
02:00:17,287 --> 02:00:21,247
I'll still do something
worthwhile with my life

1635
02:00:21,768 --> 02:00:26,761
Such frank behavior
is not good for our firm

1636
02:00:27,328 --> 02:00:31,445
We need someone diplomatic
to handle clients

1637
02:00:31,528 --> 02:00:33,802
You're too straightforward

1638
02:00:35,608 --> 02:00:36,404
But...

1639
02:00:37,528 --> 02:00:43,716
if you assure us
you'll control this attitude

1640
02:00:43,847 --> 02:00:46,725
we may consider you

1641
02:00:49,927 --> 02:00:52,965
It took two broken legs
to get me up on my feet

1642
02:00:54,768 --> 02:00:56,520
Wasn't easy to get this attitude

1643
02:00:57,207 --> 02:00:58,037
Can't change it, sir

1644
02:01:01,568 --> 02:01:06,595
You keep your job...
I'll keep my attitude

1645
02:01:06,728 --> 02:01:08,046
I'm sorry, no offense, sir

1646
02:01:12,247 --> 02:01:13,078
Wait

1647
02:01:14,967 --> 02:01:18,801
I've interviewed countless
candidates for 25 years

1648
02:01:19,207 --> 02:01:21,961
Everyone turns into
a yes-man to get the job

1649
02:01:22,127 --> 02:01:23,447
Where did you spring from, son?

1650
02:01:25,287 --> 02:01:26,083
Sir?

1651
02:01:26,328 --> 02:01:28,841
Shall we discuss the salary?

1652
02:01:36,087 --> 02:01:36,963
Thank you, sir

1653
02:02:08,207 --> 02:02:12,247
Your Majesty, thou art great

1654
02:02:14,087 --> 02:02:15,680
Accept this humble offering

1655
02:02:50,807 --> 02:02:54,118
Govind!

1656
02:02:56,087 --> 02:02:59,444
You had said, 'If he gets a job,
shave it off'

1657
02:03:06,368 --> 02:03:07,356
What have you done?

1658
02:03:10,807 --> 02:03:14,083
I feel naked without
my moustache

1659
02:03:16,287 --> 02:03:18,118
I've lost my dignity

1660
02:03:20,127 --> 02:03:22,483
I won't accept defeat, Rastogi

1661
02:03:23,728 --> 02:03:27,606
The job isn't yours until you
pass your final exam

1662
02:03:29,007 --> 02:03:32,796
And this time,
I will set the question paper

1663
02:03:35,847 --> 02:03:38,362
Dad, that's not fair

1664
02:03:40,608 --> 02:03:43,997
Everything is fair in
Love and War

1665
02:03:44,488 --> 02:03:47,685
And this is World War... III

1666
02:03:49,087 --> 02:03:50,077
Rastogi, you're dead meat;

1667
02:03:54,847 --> 02:03:55,724
Hey

1668
02:03:58,047 --> 02:03:58,923
What're you doing here?

1669
02:04:01,768 --> 02:04:02,597
Be careful

1670
02:04:08,047 --> 02:04:11,756
You've been drinking
- Yup, had to down a couple

1671
02:04:12,287 --> 02:04:14,404
A couple too many;

1672
02:04:14,488 --> 02:04:16,319
Needed the guts
- For what?

1673
02:04:18,007 --> 02:04:19,487
For stealing this
- What's this?

1674
02:04:20,528 --> 02:04:24,520
The duplicate key to
Virus's office

1675
02:04:26,927 --> 02:04:29,158
The question paper's
in a cover with a red seal

1676
02:04:29,807 --> 02:04:33,641
Dad has set it, to fail Raju

1677
02:04:33,927 --> 02:04:34,837
Go get it;

1678
02:04:35,847 --> 02:04:38,315
Are you mad or what -
that's cheating;

1679
02:04:42,608 --> 02:04:45,725
Everything's fair in
Love and War

1680
02:04:47,167 --> 02:04:48,157
Tell me something...

1681
02:04:50,007 --> 02:04:51,157
Do you really feel...

1682
02:04:52,648 --> 02:04:57,961
the noses collide while kissing?

1683
02:05:03,167 --> 02:05:06,762
Wait. Have some dhokla

1684
02:05:09,127 --> 02:05:11,641
You Gujaratis are so cute

1685
02:05:12,528 --> 02:05:15,725
But why does your food
sound so dangerous?

1686
02:05:16,768 --> 02:05:21,796
Dhokla, Fafda, Handwa,
Thepla, Khakhra

1687
02:05:22,847 --> 02:05:24,917
Sound like missiles

1688
02:05:24,967 --> 02:05:25,797
C'mon

1689
02:05:26,007 --> 02:05:28,396
'Today Bush dropped
two Dhoklas on Iraq'

1690
02:05:29,007 --> 02:05:31,761
'400 dead, 200 injured'

1691
02:05:32,087 --> 02:05:32,963
C'mon

1692
02:05:36,287 --> 02:05:37,243
Oh...

1693
02:05:38,688 --> 02:05:42,966
I can deal with Khakhra, Fafda.
But your name...

1694
02:05:43,847 --> 02:05:47,045
'Ranchhoddas Shamaldas
Chanchad': Yuck

1695
02:05:48,207 --> 02:05:50,676
I won't change my last name
after marriage

1696
02:05:52,448 --> 02:05:55,326
Pia, we can't get married

1697
02:05:58,728 --> 02:05:59,604
Why?

1698
02:06:00,408 --> 02:06:01,806
Is there someone else?

1699
02:06:04,207 --> 02:06:05,037
No

1700
02:06:05,328 --> 02:06:07,000
Are you gay?
- No

1701
02:06:08,768 --> 02:06:10,599
Then why don't you
propose to me?

1702
02:06:14,967 --> 02:06:16,367
Are you impotent?
- No

1703
02:06:18,927 --> 02:06:20,680
Then prove it

1704
02:06:21,127 --> 02:06:22,037
Pia, no

1705
02:06:22,287 --> 02:06:23,686
Stop, stop;

1706
02:06:23,847 --> 02:06:26,122
What happened?
- We didn't inform Pia

1707
02:06:26,568 --> 02:06:28,559
Stop here,
my bladders are bursting

1708
02:06:28,608 --> 02:06:30,404
Shut up!
- Are you in touch with her?

1709
02:06:30,688 --> 02:06:33,725
No... I have her home number
Then call her, I'll stop

1710
02:06:39,927 --> 02:06:40,724
Hello

1711
02:06:40,807 --> 02:06:42,957
No place for urine-expulsion
in this country

1712
02:06:43,007 --> 02:06:46,283
Hello, is Pia there?
- No, she's not

1713
02:06:46,648 --> 02:06:48,365
Is she at the hospital?

1714
02:06:48,488 --> 02:06:50,001
Why would she be there?

1715
02:06:50,207 --> 02:06:52,323
She's getting married today -
in Manali

1716
02:07:00,007 --> 02:07:01,202
Too late! She's married

1717
02:07:02,568 --> 02:07:05,365
Not yet. It's a six hour drive

1718
02:07:05,688 --> 02:07:07,679
If we rush, we'll reach
before the vows

1719
02:07:08,167 --> 02:07:08,997
What do you say?

1720
02:07:10,847 --> 02:07:13,203
It's a no-brainer. Let's turn back

1721
02:07:13,408 --> 02:07:15,079
No turning back

1722
02:07:15,528 --> 02:07:18,167
Straight to Ladakh.
We'll meet Rancho and return

1723
02:07:18,328 --> 02:07:20,796
I have a Friday meeting with
Phunsukh Wangdu

1724
02:07:20,927 --> 02:07:22,407
Get into the car

1725
02:07:22,608 --> 02:07:25,485
If I miss my meeting,
the Japanese will get him

1726
02:07:25,688 --> 02:07:28,645
They're offering him a
first name in the company

1727
02:07:28,768 --> 02:07:30,962
'Phunsukh and Fujiyashi',
profit sharing...

1728
02:08:03,247 --> 02:08:05,318
Pia weds Suhas;
- Thanks for the suit

1729
02:08:07,568 --> 02:08:09,001
Virus will have a heart attack

1730
02:08:10,047 --> 02:08:12,641
At every daughter's wedding,
we're there to rock the party

1731
02:08:14,007 --> 02:08:17,283
Listen, I'll update Pia,
you peel off the price tag

1732
02:08:33,408 --> 02:08:35,557
Farhan
- We found Rancho

1733
02:08:43,368 --> 02:08:44,926
For Room 107?
- Yes, sir

1734
02:08:45,608 --> 02:08:48,327
You've taken ages
- Sorry, sir

1735
02:08:48,448 --> 02:08:49,278
Off, now

1736
02:08:57,967 --> 02:08:59,605
Housekeeping, sir
- Come in

1737
02:09:00,127 --> 02:09:02,641
Amore... Amore...

1738
02:09:02,728 --> 02:09:04,046
Quick, iron my coat

1739
02:09:04,127 --> 02:09:06,846
Amore... Amore...

1740
02:09:07,688 --> 02:09:10,805
We found Rancho!
Now you can't marry this ass

1741
02:09:11,287 --> 02:09:12,323
You're mad, Farhan

1742
02:09:13,408 --> 02:09:15,967
Don't fool yourself, Pia.
You still love Rancho

1743
02:09:16,167 --> 02:09:18,045
You're still eating his favorite food

1744
02:09:18,328 --> 02:09:20,841
Amore... Amore...

1745
02:09:35,648 --> 02:09:39,686
He's incorrigible.
Once a price tag, always a price tag

1746
02:09:39,768 --> 02:09:42,520
Shut up, Farhan.
Suhas is a changed man

1747
02:09:43,047 --> 02:09:44,958
He doesn't speak of
brands and prices anymore

1748
02:09:45,007 --> 02:09:48,079
My 150,000/: coat

1749
02:09:48,167 --> 02:09:50,203
Why do you people eat sauce?

1750
02:09:50,247 --> 02:09:52,636
I'll sort it out, sir
- How?

1751
02:09:52,728 --> 02:09:55,195
Our laundry specializes in
cleaning mint-stained suits

1752
02:09:55,328 --> 02:09:57,238
I'll clean it in a jiffy

1753
02:10:02,328 --> 02:10:03,601
Get it soon

1754
02:10:04,528 --> 02:10:06,677
But it's too late now, Farhan
- Pia

1755
02:10:07,528 --> 02:10:09,677
Let's go, Pia, we're late

1756
02:10:20,648 --> 02:10:23,845
Pia, it's me... Raju.
Don't yell, they'll kill me

1757
02:10:28,807 --> 02:10:29,684
Where is Suhas?

1758
02:10:29,728 --> 02:10:32,367
Housekeeping took my coat

1759
02:10:32,807 --> 02:10:34,525
Go... Send Suhas here

1760
02:10:34,728 --> 02:10:37,800
It's rude to leave the ceremony

1761
02:10:48,648 --> 02:10:50,239
Yeah, Farhan?
- The car's ready

1762
02:10:50,568 --> 02:10:53,082
Grab her hand and run.
Don't move

1763
02:10:54,528 --> 02:10:56,086
Sir...
- My coat?

1764
02:10:56,127 --> 02:10:57,247
You're here...

1765
02:10:57,247 --> 02:10:58,966
So who's at the altar?
- Altar?

1766
02:11:01,167 --> 02:11:03,556
Another couple of rounds,
and we'll be considered married

1767
02:11:03,728 --> 02:11:05,922
I'm already married, Pia.
Let's go

1768
02:11:06,368 --> 02:11:09,519
It's too late.
People will laugh at me

1769
02:11:09,768 --> 02:11:11,485
So you'll commit suicide?

1770
02:11:12,047 --> 02:11:12,923
Rastogi;

1771
02:11:13,007 --> 02:11:15,043
People will gossip briefly,
then forget

1772
02:11:16,368 --> 02:11:19,328
But you... you'll regret
on your deathbed

1773
02:11:19,328 --> 02:11:22,161
that the car was at the gate,
Rancho within reach...

1774
02:11:22,328 --> 02:11:25,684
but in fear of people,
you married this ass

1775
02:11:27,768 --> 02:11:28,677
Housekeeping?

1776
02:12:06,807 --> 02:12:09,720
Pia, minor problem

1777
02:12:10,007 --> 02:12:10,837
What?

1778
02:12:11,247 --> 02:12:12,805
We don't know if Rancho's married

1779
02:12:12,847 --> 02:12:13,677
What;

1780
02:12:13,768 --> 02:12:16,328
He won't be married
- And if he is?

1781
02:12:17,167 --> 02:12:18,520
Then we'll drop you back

1782
02:12:19,368 --> 02:12:22,997
Relax! Handmade biscuit?

1783
02:12:26,688 --> 02:12:27,518
What's he doing here?

1784
02:12:28,528 --> 02:12:31,804
Ignore him
- The biscuit's very good

1785
02:12:32,807 --> 02:12:34,604
Till yesterday,
I was a law-abiding citizen

1786
02:12:35,087 --> 02:12:38,796
But in the last 24 hours,
I'd grounded an aircraft

1787
02:12:39,568 --> 02:12:41,922
almost assigned Shamaldas's
ashes to the sewers, and

1788
02:12:42,167 --> 02:12:46,399
made a bride elope from her
own wedding! All for Rancho

1789
02:12:47,807 --> 02:12:49,844
But he too would do
anything for friends

1790
02:12:50,087 --> 02:12:53,444
Like stealing the question paper...
from the lion's den

1791
02:12:53,528 --> 02:12:54,516
Envelope with the red seal

1792
02:12:55,488 --> 02:13:00,278
He feared that if Raju failed,
there'd be another high jump

1793
02:13:03,328 --> 02:13:08,402
We were principled thieves,
stealing the paper only for Raju

1794
02:13:08,768 --> 02:13:09,837
We'd sworn we won't even
take a peek

1795
02:13:12,448 --> 02:13:13,721
Where's it hidden...

1796
02:13:13,847 --> 02:13:17,363
We'll grow old searching;
Ask Pia

1797
02:13:23,328 --> 02:13:24,443
Pia, your phone

1798
02:13:25,648 --> 02:13:28,765
Mr. Papa-To-Be;
If you say 'All is well', he kicks

1799
02:13:28,847 --> 02:13:29,644
He kicked

1800
02:13:32,007 --> 02:13:33,440
Pia, your phone

1801
02:13:39,047 --> 02:13:40,242
Found it! Rancho

1802
02:13:41,648 --> 02:13:42,603
Hello?

1803
02:14:00,287 --> 02:14:02,438
Quick, photocopy this

1804
02:14:22,768 --> 02:14:23,518
Where was it?

1805
02:14:23,807 --> 02:14:24,762
Put it back

1806
02:14:47,167 --> 02:14:49,123
We're safe!
- Where were you?

1807
02:14:53,528 --> 02:14:55,166
Here
- What's this?

1808
02:14:55,488 --> 02:14:56,363
A gift

1809
02:14:57,448 --> 02:15:01,202
Question paper.
Virus set it himself, to fail you

1810
02:15:08,488 --> 02:15:09,761
Strange buddies;

1811
02:15:11,047 --> 02:15:15,439
First teach you to be upright,
then offer a path to shame

1812
02:15:17,408 --> 02:15:18,396
No way

1813
02:15:19,927 --> 02:15:21,247
If I pass,
it'll be on my own steam

1814
02:15:24,967 --> 02:15:26,082
If I don't, it's still ok

1815
02:15:42,608 --> 02:15:46,965
He'd won us over!
I felt like embracing him as family...

1816
02:15:47,847 --> 02:15:49,679
but then I controlled my emotions

1817
02:16:08,007 --> 02:16:10,841
Damn thief
- Sir, please, sir

1818
02:16:11,007 --> 02:16:14,079
Rascal
- Sorry sir

1819
02:16:14,608 --> 02:16:15,836
Wanted to change the system

1820
02:16:17,488 --> 02:16:22,243
You'll pee on my door
- Sir, what're you doing

1821
02:16:23,688 --> 02:16:24,643
Sorry sir

1822
02:16:26,047 --> 02:16:27,845
You are rusticated!

1823
02:16:28,608 --> 02:16:31,485
If all of you aren't out by morning,
I'll call the police

1824
02:16:31,847 --> 02:16:33,166
I will call the police;

1825
02:16:35,567 --> 02:16:36,363
Rascals;

1826
02:16:36,688 --> 02:16:37,961
Rascals, all of you

1827
02:16:41,808 --> 02:16:44,038
How did he get my office key?

1828
02:16:45,288 --> 02:16:46,640
I gave him the key, Dad

1829
02:16:47,968 --> 02:16:51,608
I wish I'd given this key to
my brother... He'd be alive today

1830
02:16:51,608 --> 02:16:52,484
Stop it, Pia

1831
02:16:53,567 --> 02:16:56,287
You think your son
fell off a train and died?

1832
02:16:56,808 --> 02:16:57,683
Shut up, Pia

1833
02:16:57,768 --> 02:16:59,962
You decided he'd be an engineer

1834
02:17:00,128 --> 02:17:02,323
Did you ever ask him
what he wanted to be?

1835
02:17:03,087 --> 02:17:04,601
You put such pressure on him...

1836
02:17:04,968 --> 02:17:07,163
that he chose death
over the entrance exam

1837
02:17:11,247 --> 02:17:12,077
I don't understand...

1838
02:17:12,847 --> 02:17:15,316
Dad, you go to your room

1839
02:17:19,048 --> 02:17:21,323
Pia, don't do this

1840
02:17:23,688 --> 02:17:27,441
He wanted to study Literature,
be a writer

1841
02:17:29,608 --> 02:17:31,996
But all he wrote was
this suicide note

1842
02:17:32,048 --> 02:17:33,275
Put that away, please

1843
02:17:33,448 --> 02:17:35,040
No more cover-ups!

1844
02:17:38,288 --> 02:17:41,405
Just once...

1845
02:17:41,448 --> 02:17:44,996
if you'd said: Don't do Engineering
if you don't want to

1846
02:17:45,808 --> 02:17:47,161
just do what your heart is in

1847
02:17:48,567 --> 02:17:50,239
then he'd be alive today

1848
02:17:57,847 --> 02:17:59,838
He didn't commit suicide

1849
02:18:00,528 --> 02:18:01,483
You're right, Dad

1850
02:18:02,968 --> 02:18:04,162
It wasn't suicide...

1851
02:18:06,528 --> 02:18:07,563
It was murder

1852
02:18:22,847 --> 02:18:25,601
Many city roads are
completely submerged

1853
02:18:25,647 --> 02:18:27,558
Traffic has come to a standstill

1854
02:18:40,927 --> 02:18:44,602
Dad...

1855
02:18:45,647 --> 02:18:46,558
Mona?

1856
02:18:50,567 --> 02:18:52,957
Go back, Millimeter.
Why're you following us?

1857
02:18:53,487 --> 02:18:55,683
Why?
Your pop owns the road?

1858
02:18:55,808 --> 02:18:57,445
Please help,
we are desperate here;

1859
02:18:58,368 --> 02:19:00,165
You can't send an ambulance?

1860
02:19:01,128 --> 02:19:02,959
Get it from another hospital

1861
02:19:03,567 --> 02:19:06,958
The entire city's flooded, sir.
We're helpless

1862
02:19:10,327 --> 02:19:11,556
Mona, you ok?

1863
02:19:12,087 --> 02:19:13,042
Rancho, Pia

1864
02:19:15,327 --> 02:19:19,037
Rancho, you can't reach here.
Do as I say

1865
02:19:19,327 --> 02:19:24,004
The water bag has burst

1866
02:19:24,968 --> 02:19:27,402
Disconnected! Mona

1867
02:19:32,407 --> 02:19:33,362
Mona!

1868
02:19:37,567 --> 02:19:39,047
Turn on the lights
- Where to?

1869
02:19:39,528 --> 02:19:43,316
To the table tennis table
- Pia, we're in the common room

1870
02:19:47,128 --> 02:19:48,924
Raju, turn on the web camera

1871
02:19:54,808 --> 02:19:55,923
Where's Mona? Show me

1872
02:19:57,407 --> 02:19:58,317
Hold on

1873
02:20:00,448 --> 02:20:01,278
Here, Pia

1874
02:20:01,567 --> 02:20:04,365
Mona, don't worry. I'm with you

1875
02:20:04,448 --> 02:20:05,403
Pia, I'm dying!

1876
02:20:05,768 --> 02:20:08,281
Rancho, even when
there were no hospitals or docs

1877
02:20:08,407 --> 02:20:09,761
babies were delivered

1878
02:20:10,327 --> 02:20:12,558
You all will deliver this baby

1879
02:20:15,128 --> 02:20:16,640
All is well

1880
02:20:16,768 --> 02:20:19,646
How dare you? I'll kill you

1881
02:20:19,768 --> 02:20:21,724
Dad, stay out of this

1882
02:20:22,647 --> 02:20:24,718
Farhan, get towels and scissors

1883
02:20:24,768 --> 02:20:27,156
Millimeter, get clothes clips
and hot water

1884
02:20:27,407 --> 02:20:28,841
Rancho, cover Mona

1885
02:20:36,087 --> 02:20:37,566
Mona, try pushing

1886
02:20:37,968 --> 02:20:41,755
Push with all your might

1887
02:20:42,007 --> 02:20:44,316
Stop it! I can't do it

1888
02:20:44,528 --> 02:20:46,280
Rancho, check if there's crowning

1889
02:20:47,167 --> 02:20:47,997
Crowning...?

1890
02:20:49,288 --> 02:20:50,164
Get that diagram

1891
02:20:52,968 --> 02:20:55,606
See if the head is coming out

1892
02:20:57,847 --> 02:20:59,121
Check quickly

1893
02:20:59,847 --> 02:21:00,757
Go;

1894
02:21:01,407 --> 02:21:03,797
Go, Rancho, go

1895
02:21:10,768 --> 02:21:12,804
No crowning

1896
02:21:12,847 --> 02:21:14,679
Mona, please push

1897
02:21:17,247 --> 02:21:18,077
Mona!

1898
02:21:20,968 --> 02:21:22,083
She's tired, Pia

1899
02:21:22,487 --> 02:21:26,037
Wake her! If she won't push,
it's a big problem

1900
02:21:26,368 --> 02:21:29,996
They need a vacuum cup
- Where will they get one?

1901
02:21:30,167 --> 02:21:32,921
What's a vacuum cup?
How is it used?

1902
02:21:33,167 --> 02:21:33,997
I'll show you

1903
02:21:37,128 --> 02:21:41,280
If the mother's too fatigued to push,
a cup is placed on baby's head

1904
02:21:41,567 --> 02:21:45,197
Suction makes the cup
stick to the head...

1905
02:21:45,847 --> 02:21:47,679
and the baby is pulled out

1906
02:21:48,128 --> 02:21:50,244
I can make this
- How?

1907
02:21:50,487 --> 02:21:52,239
With a vacuum cleaner
- Vacuum cleaner?

1908
02:21:52,288 --> 02:21:53,323
Yes

1909
02:21:53,368 --> 02:21:55,643
That pressure's too high

1910
02:21:55,688 --> 02:21:57,757
I'll control it
- D'you have a vacuum cleaner?

1911
02:21:57,808 --> 02:21:58,843
Yes, in my office

1912
02:21:59,247 --> 02:22:01,842
Farhan, rush and get it
- Here's the key

1913
02:22:07,608 --> 02:22:10,917
Mona, push

1914
02:22:11,647 --> 02:22:13,127
Oh my God

1915
02:22:13,968 --> 02:22:14,843
What happened?

1916
02:22:19,528 --> 02:22:21,722
Raju, what happened?
- The power's gone

1917
02:22:22,647 --> 02:22:24,047
How'll the vacuum work now?

1918
02:22:24,087 --> 02:22:26,556
Farhan, you get the vacuum,
I'll get the power.

1919
02:22:26,608 --> 02:22:27,563
How?

1920
02:22:28,208 --> 02:22:29,640
Millimeter, get Virus out

1921
02:22:30,968 --> 02:22:33,528
What nonsense is this!

1922
02:22:33,727 --> 02:22:37,164
Not this Virus.
My Virus, the inverter

1923
02:22:37,327 --> 02:22:39,158
Get that, quick
- Ok

1924
02:22:39,407 --> 02:22:41,477
Raju, wake up the hostel

1925
02:22:41,647 --> 02:22:44,480
Get car batteries, wires,
and a vacuum gauge

1926
02:22:47,208 --> 02:22:49,768
Emergency in the common room!

1927
02:23:19,327 --> 02:23:21,363
Where's Rancho?
- Here, sir

1928
02:23:21,608 --> 02:23:24,201
Keep the batteries here
...and the wires

1929
02:23:26,368 --> 02:23:29,440
Raju, switch off everything,
connect the inverter to the mains

1930
02:23:34,048 --> 02:23:35,197
Rancho, vacuum cleaner

1931
02:23:36,288 --> 02:23:39,085
Farhan, get your lens cleaner

1932
02:23:39,128 --> 02:23:40,527
Blower?
- Yeah, get it

1933
02:23:43,128 --> 02:23:44,117
Rancho, blower

1934
02:23:44,247 --> 02:23:46,203
Good. Fix this to the gauge

1935
02:24:11,528 --> 02:24:12,755
Rancho, I'm done

1936
02:24:15,087 --> 02:24:16,202
All switches off?
- Yes

1937
02:24:17,688 --> 02:24:19,245
Hit the table
and computer switches

1938
02:24:19,288 --> 02:24:20,118
Ok

1939
02:24:32,288 --> 02:24:33,356
Raju, turn on the computer

1940
02:24:33,727 --> 02:24:35,365
Farhan, here

1941
02:24:37,368 --> 02:24:39,324
Pia, come here quick

1942
02:24:41,688 --> 02:24:42,756
Love you, Rancho

1943
02:24:43,487 --> 02:24:45,398
Farhan, turn it on
- Ok

1944
02:24:51,688 --> 02:24:53,644
Pia, how much suction?

1945
02:24:54,007 --> 02:24:55,406
Not more than 0.5

1946
02:24:55,608 --> 02:24:57,564
Farhan, 0.5
- Cover it

1947
02:24:59,048 --> 02:24:59,924
0.5

1948
02:25:02,368 --> 02:25:06,246
Vacuum cleaner baby!
Mother of all deliveries

1949
02:25:07,288 --> 02:25:08,084
Farhan, stop

1950
02:25:08,128 --> 02:25:08,924
Ok

1951
02:25:15,167 --> 02:25:16,361
Raju, get on the table

1952
02:25:16,608 --> 02:25:19,645
Push the baby down, like this

1953
02:25:19,808 --> 02:25:20,718
Ok

1954
02:25:21,768 --> 02:25:22,644
Farhan, turn it on

1955
02:25:27,048 --> 02:25:29,278
C'mon, you can do it

1956
02:25:30,368 --> 02:25:32,722
C'mon, push

1957
02:25:36,727 --> 02:25:39,195
Do it for Champ

1958
02:25:39,407 --> 02:25:41,763
C'mon, Mona

1959
02:25:43,407 --> 02:25:45,398
He's coming out;

1960
02:25:46,688 --> 02:25:48,406
You can do it

1961
02:25:49,167 --> 02:25:51,442
Yes Mona, push

1962
02:25:58,968 --> 02:26:00,003
Farhan, turn it off

1963
02:26:00,087 --> 02:26:01,076
Ok, off

1964
02:26:20,528 --> 02:26:22,245
Two clips,
cut the umbilical cord

1965
02:26:22,528 --> 02:26:24,644
Farhan, two clips on the cord

1966
02:26:25,327 --> 02:26:27,283
Get scissors
- Be careful

1967
02:26:28,448 --> 02:26:30,643
Cut at the center,
get a towel

1968
02:26:33,327 --> 02:26:35,558
Pia, he's not crying

1969
02:26:39,647 --> 02:26:42,445
Hey Champ!

1970
02:26:43,727 --> 02:26:46,083
Rancho, rub his back

1971
02:26:48,247 --> 02:26:50,203
Hey Champ
- Come on, Champ

1972
02:26:51,968 --> 02:26:54,004
No, nothing

1973
02:26:54,448 --> 02:26:55,436
Blow air into his mouth

1974
02:27:02,327 --> 02:27:03,123
C'mon, Champ

1975
02:27:08,448 --> 02:27:09,278
No response

1976
02:27:32,647 --> 02:27:36,118
Hush Mona, say -
All is well

1977
02:27:41,167 --> 02:27:42,077
He kicked

1978
02:27:43,327 --> 02:27:44,157
What?

1979
02:27:45,007 --> 02:27:46,236
He kicked

1980
02:27:49,567 --> 02:27:50,842
Say: All is well

1981
02:27:51,727 --> 02:27:59,042
All is well

1982
02:28:38,808 --> 02:28:42,039
If Virus had said, 'My grandson
will be an engineer'

1983
02:28:42,167 --> 02:28:43,965
I would've broken his jaw

1984
02:28:44,608 --> 02:28:47,326
But when he finally spoke,
he stunned us

1985
02:28:47,608 --> 02:28:50,645
What a kick!
Wanna be a footballer?

1986
02:28:51,647 --> 02:28:54,559
Be what you want to be

1987
02:29:10,368 --> 02:29:14,121
Wait: I've not finished with you!

1988
02:29:16,407 --> 02:29:18,842
First day of college,
you'd asked me a question...

1989
02:29:19,208 --> 02:29:21,516
Why didn't astronauts
use a pencil in space?

1990
02:29:22,247 --> 02:29:24,442
If a pencil tip breaks

1991
02:29:24,608 --> 02:29:30,284
it'd float in zero gravity.
Get into eyes, nose, instruments...

1992
02:29:30,407 --> 02:29:32,284
You were wrong

1993
02:29:33,808 --> 02:29:35,604
You cannot be right all the time

1994
02:29:37,608 --> 02:29:38,596
You understand?

1995
02:29:40,927 --> 02:29:41,757
Yes, sir

1996
02:29:42,968 --> 02:29:45,004
This was an important invention

1997
02:29:46,247 --> 02:29:47,236
You understand?

1998
02:29:48,567 --> 02:29:49,397
Yes, sir

1999
02:29:51,768 --> 02:30:00,675
My Director said, 'When you find
an extraordinary student...'

2000
02:30:18,007 --> 02:30:22,286
Go, study;
Pass your exams and leave

2001
02:30:30,808 --> 02:30:32,843
And now, Student of the Year...

2002
02:30:33,048 --> 02:30:35,436
Ranchhoddas Shamaldas Chanchad

2003
02:30:52,368 --> 02:30:53,641
Sir, one photo

2004
02:31:10,407 --> 02:31:13,718
I wanted to capture all these
memories and take them home

2005
02:31:15,688 --> 02:31:20,842
That day, we hugged,
we rejoiced, we cried...

2006
02:31:21,128 --> 02:31:22,719
We vowed that we'd meet
at least once a year...

2007
02:31:23,368 --> 02:31:26,677
Who knew then, we were seeing
Rancho for the last time

2008
02:31:59,247 --> 02:32:00,157
Untie him

2009
02:32:03,368 --> 02:32:05,199
I'll sue you all in an
American court

2010
02:32:19,087 --> 02:32:19,917
Raju

2011
02:32:38,167 --> 02:32:40,078
Only Rancho can create
a school like this

2012
02:32:40,608 --> 02:32:41,643
But where is he?

2013
02:32:45,927 --> 02:32:47,121
Don't pee here

2014
02:32:48,167 --> 02:32:49,726
Go away creatures

2015
02:32:50,087 --> 02:32:53,046
Don't pee here
- I'll smack you

2016
02:33:10,087 --> 02:33:12,203
Bingo; He cannot be far

2017
02:33:23,208 --> 02:33:25,403
Excuse me,
where is Ranchhoddas?

2018
02:33:25,528 --> 02:33:27,439
He's not Ranchhoddas!
- Rancho...

2019
02:33:27,528 --> 02:33:29,644
Chhote... Dammit,
what's his name?

2020
02:33:29,768 --> 02:33:32,361
Calm down. Come with me

2021
02:33:34,727 --> 02:33:35,603
Where's he?
- Rancho

2022
02:33:42,688 --> 02:33:45,725
Farhan, he's read all your books

2023
02:33:51,768 --> 02:33:57,558
Raju, he reads your blog everyday.
Proudly shares it with the kids

2024
02:34:00,927 --> 02:34:04,283
Remember your helmet, Pia?
It was stolen...

2025
02:34:06,128 --> 02:34:09,200
Who are you?
How do you know us?

2026
02:34:09,448 --> 02:34:11,439
Didn't you recognize me?
- No

2027
02:34:12,327 --> 02:34:16,162
How would you?
Millimeter is now Centimeter

2028
02:34:21,007 --> 02:34:25,319
Not Centimeter, you're Kilometer

2029
02:34:26,128 --> 02:34:27,083
How did you get here?

2030
02:34:27,167 --> 02:34:30,284
I got a letter with
a train ticket inside

2031
02:34:30,528 --> 02:34:34,122
It said: 'Miss being in school?
Catch this train'... I did

2032
02:34:35,647 --> 02:34:36,717
That rascal Rancho;

2033
02:34:40,727 --> 02:34:41,683
Where is that idiot?

2034
02:34:52,407 --> 02:34:54,238
Dorje, you fly it

2035
02:35:08,608 --> 02:35:13,841
Every night you ride into my dreams
on a scooter, dressed as a bride

2036
02:35:14,768 --> 02:35:16,962
Instead of a veil,
you lift your helmet

2037
02:35:17,567 --> 02:35:20,207
and come close to kiss me

2038
02:35:23,647 --> 02:35:24,842
Couldn't you tell me
before leaving?

2039
02:35:27,087 --> 02:35:27,837
No

2040
02:35:29,608 --> 02:35:30,484
Sorry

2041
02:35:30,847 --> 02:35:31,644
Did you marry?

2042
02:35:32,208 --> 02:35:36,281
What? No

2043
02:35:37,208 --> 02:35:39,721
You?
- Almost... Idiot

2044
02:35:47,007 --> 02:35:47,837
So?

2045
02:35:49,247 --> 02:35:50,202
So what?

2046
02:35:50,688 --> 02:35:51,961
Do you love someone?

2047
02:35:56,208 --> 02:35:57,004
Yes

2048
02:36:02,808 --> 02:36:03,638
Who?

2049
02:36:04,847 --> 02:36:05,724
You

